# FeedService

Rust microservice for personal home feeds. Uses a fan-out-on-write strategy: when a post is created, FeedService inserts one row per follower into Cassandra `user_feed`. Rows expire automatically after 30 days via a TTL.

---

## Architecture

```
PostService ──post.created──▶ MQTT Broker
                                    │
                                    ▼
                             FeedService :3005
                                    │
                         ┌──────────┴───────────┐
                         │                      │
                     Cassandra              Cassandra
                    (user_feed)         (user_followers)
                    write fan-out        enumerate followers
```

On a `post.created` event: FeedService reads all followers of the post author from `user_followers`, then inserts one `user_feed` row for each follower.

---

## HTTP Endpoints

All endpoints are prefixed `/api/feed/` by Nginx.

---

### `GET /` 🔒

Return the personal feed for the authenticated user, newest first.

**Query parameters:**

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| `before`  | —       | Cursor: ISO 8601 timestamp — return items older than this |
| `limit`   | 20      | Max results (max 100) |

**Response `200`:**
```json
[
  {
    "post_id": "<uuid>",
    "author_id": "<uuid>",
    "author_name": "bob",
    "restaurant_id": "134469",
    "restaurant_name": "Le Gabriel - La Réserve Paris",
    "media_type": "photo",
    "media_url": "/api/download/files/abc.jpg",
    "thumbnail_url": null,
    "caption": "Best meal of my life.",
    "rating": "GOOD",
    "created_at": "2024-03-10T18:22:00Z"
  }
]
```

---

### `GET /health`

Liveness probe. Returns `200 ok`.

---

## Cassandra Tables

### `user_feed`
Partition key: `viewer_id` — one partition per user, all their feed items.
Clustering: `created_at DESC, post_id ASC` — reads are newest-first.
TTL: **30 days** (`default_time_to_live = 2592000`) — old entries expire automatically without maintenance.

```
viewer_id       uuid  (partition)
created_at      timestamp  (cluster desc)
post_id         uuid  (cluster asc)
author_id       uuid
author_name     text
restaurant_id   text
restaurant_name text
media_type      text
media_url       text
thumbnail_url   text
caption         text
rating          text   -- "GOOD" | "BAD"
```

### `user_followers` (read-only, written by UserService)
Used to enumerate whom to fan-out to on `post.created`.

---

## MQTT Subscriptions

| Topic          | Action |
|----------------|--------|
| `post.created` | Read author's followers from `user_followers`, insert one `user_feed` row per follower |

---

## Configuration

```env
CASSANDRA_NODES=localhost:9042
HTTP_ADDR=0.0.0.0:3005
JWT_SECRET=changeme
MQTT_HOST=localhost
MQTT_PORT=1883
MQTT_CLIENT_ID=feed-service
RUST_LOG=info
```

---

## Local Development

```bash
cp .env.example .env
cargo run
```

---

## Project Structure

```
FeedService/
├── src/
│   ├── main.rs     # Entry point
│   ├── config.rs   # Env-var config
│   ├── db_cql.rs   # Cassandra: get_feed, get_followers, insert_feed_item
│   ├── models.rs   # FeedItem
│   ├── auth.rs     # JWT middleware
│   ├── http.rs     # Axum router + get_feed handler
│   ├── mqtt.rs     # MQTT subscriber — post.created fan-out
│   └── error.rs    # AppError → HTTP response
├── Cargo.toml
└── .env.example
```
